SIMPLE: embodiment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embodiment
<hw>Em*bod"i*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of embodying; the state of being embodied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which embodies or is embodied; representation
in a physical body; a completely organized system, like the body;
<as>as, the <ex>embodiment</ex> of courage, or of courtesy; the
<ex>embodiment</ex> of true piety.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embody</ent>⟦br⟧
